article.headline: Yale 52, Princeton 51
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Matt Pinick put back his own blocked shot with 11 seconds left, allowing Yale to escape with a wild 52-51 victory over Princeton on Saturday night. Pinick also was fouled on the play, but he missed the free throw. Teammate Matt Kyle got the rebound, but his putback attempt missed and Princeton's Marcus Schroeder grabbed the ball. He then dribbled down the left side and tried a short jumper, but it rolled off the rim as time expired. Schroeder had given the Tigers a 51-50 lead when he scored off an offensive rebound with 21.6 seconds left. After a timeout, Yale got the ball to Pinick and he tried to drive the lane, but his shot blocked by Kyle Koncz. The ball, though, bounced right back to Pinick, who then scored his game-winner. Pinick finished with 12 points for the Bulldogs (14-13, 10-4 in Ivy League), while Kyle and Eric Flato each had 13 points. Schroeder led the Tigers (11-16, 2-11) with a career-high 17 points and six rebounds, while Noah Savage added 15 points. Yale clinched second place in the conference and earned 10 league wins for just the eighth time in its history, while the loss guarantees that Princeton will finish in last place.
